President Cyril Ramaphosa. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - South Africa’s tenure as Chair of the African Union comes to an end on Saturday. President Cyril Ramaphosa will hand over the reins to President Felix Tshisekedi of the Democratic Republic of Congo. The president is accompanied by a large number of cabinet ministers. READ: COVID-19 and conflicts compete for attention at African Union summit He says among the notable achievements during his tenure was getting the African Continental Free Trade Area off the ground. But, there have been concerns over Tshisekedi's capacity to chair the AU. He still faces battles at home to consolidate his power. 